value.name: Visit California
value.snippet: Find things to do, places to visit, and experiences to explore at Visit California, the Golden State’s official tourism site. Learn about national parks, hotels, restaurants, beaches, mountains, cities, and more.

deepLinks.name: Places to Visit
deepLinks.snippet: From misty Northern California redwood forests to sun-kissed Southern California beaches, the enchanted Golden State makes Disneyland seem normal. Discover hundreds of places to visit, learn our diverse regions and lively cities all in one place. Explore California's 12 Regions. Los Angeles County.

value.name: California | Flag, Facts, Maps, Capital, Cities, & Destinations
value.snippet: California, constituent state of the United States of America. It was admitted as the 31st state of the union on September 9, 1850, and by the early 1960s it was the most populous U.S. state.

value.name: California - Simple English Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
value.snippet: California, officially the State of California, is a state in the western part of the United States, along the Pacific Ocean. It is the third biggest US state by land area (after Alaska and Texas) with 163,696 square mi (423,970 km 2). It has more people than any other state with over 39 million people as of 2019. value.name: California 2023: Best Places to Visit - Tripadvisor
value.snippet: California is a fertile, peaceful place where you’ll find a near-equal balance of vineyards and deserts, beaches and mountains, hippies and traditionalists. Catch an epic wave in Big Sur or swirl a glass in Napa Valley. Be dazzled by the Joshua Tree night sky or just star-gaze in Hollywood.

value.name: California Maps & Facts - World Atlas
value.snippet: California is a U.S. state located on the west coast of North America, bordered by Oregon to the north, Nevada and Arizona to the east, and Mexico to the south. It covers an area of 163,696 square miles, making it the third largest state in terms of size behind Alaska and Texas.

value.name: www.ca.gov | California State Portal
value.snippet: California has been hit with devastating wildfires and other natural disasters in both the northern and southern parts of the state. If you need more information about recovery or resources visit the following resources: Emergency Services Wild Fire Recovery Disaster Assistance.

value.name: California – Wikipedia
value.snippet: California er den tredje største staten etter areal, kun mindre enn Texas og Alaska. California grenser til Oregon i nord, Nevada i øst, Arizona i sørøst, og Mexico i sør. Hovedstaden i California er Sacramento, og Los Angeles er delstatens største og USAs nest største by.

value.name: History of California - Wikipedia
value.snippet: California was one of the most culturally and linguistically diverse areas in pre-Columbian North America. After contact with Spanish explorers, many of the Native Americans died from foreign diseases and genocide campaigns.

value.name: California – Store norske leksikon
value.snippet: California er en delstat i USA. Delstaten ligger ved Stillehavet og grenser mot Oregon i nord, Nevada og Arizona i øst og mot Mexico i sør.California har et totalt areal på cirka 424 000 kvadratkilometer, og er den tredje største delstaten i USA etter Alaska og Texas.
